<div class="stats"><p>In 2020 there were <span style="color:#d97b41">68,630</span> opioid related deaths... that number has risen to <span style="color:#d97b41">80,411</span> in 2021 alone</p></div>

<div class="stats"><p>75% of all overdose deaths in 2020 involved an opioid</p></div>

<div class="stats"><p>The United States makes up 4.4% of the world's population, and consumes over 80% of the world's opioids</p></div>

<div class="stats"><p>54% of more than 200,000 physicians received a payment from pharmaceutical companies that make opioids</p></div>

<div id="statsend"><p>One kilogram of fentanyl has the potential to kill 500,000 people</p></div>

